
@startuml

class ResearchGroup {
  +String id
  +String name
  +List<WorkPackage> workPackages
  +List<Researcher> researchers
}

class WorkPackage {
  +String id
  +String name
  +ResearchGroup leaderGroup
  +List<Researcher> teamMembers
}

class Researcher {
  +String id
  +String name
  +ResearchGroup currentGroup
  +List<WorkPackage> assignedWPs
}

' Relationships
ResearchGroup "1" -- "0..*" WorkPackage : has
WorkPackage "1" -- "0..*" Researcher : has team members
Researcher "1" -- "1" ResearchGroup : belongs to
Researcher "1" -- "0..*" WorkPackage : is assigned to

@enduml

### Explanation of the Diagram:

- **`ResearchGroup`**:
  - Holds a list of `WorkPackage`s that it leads.
  - Maintains a list of `Researcher`s who belong to the group.

- **`WorkPackage`**:
  - Is led by exactly one `ResearchGroup`.
  - Has a list of `Researcher`s assigned as team members, regardless of their research group.

- **`Researcher`**:
  - Belongs to exactly one `ResearchGroup`.
  - Can be assigned to multiple `WorkPackage`s.
  - When a researcher changes groups or a `WorkPackage` leadership changes, the assignments are re-recorded to maintain traceability of service delivery.

